dc_description_s: AMS 2. Great Britain. War Office. General Staff. Geographical Section. G.S.G.S. 4375. Great Britain. War Office. General Staff. Geographical Section. G.S.G.S. 4410. Great Britain. War Office. General Staff. Geographical Section. G.S.G.S. 4412. Great Britain. War Office. General Staff. Geographical Section. G.S.G.S. 4413. Alternate title: Sibiu, Romania. Universal transverse Mercator and Danube zone grids. UTM grid added, gradient tints and isogonic data deleted and communications partially revised by AMS, 1947. Relief shown by 50 and 100 meter contour intervals and spot elevations. With a Romanian glossary. Corrected from intelligence reports to October 1942. See index. Library holdings for this set are incomplete.
dc_publisher_s: Washington, D.C. : Army Map Service, U.S. Army, 1947.
